The paper deals with graph sparsification and coarsening, which are fundamental topics in computer science and related to graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of the graph Laplacian and its inverse, which are commonly used in spectral graph theory (cs.SI). The paper mentions planar graphs, which are a subfield of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the use of synthetic models and real-world datasets, which are commonly used in numerical analysis and scientific computing (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of existing methods for graph coarsening and sparsification, which is related to machine learning and data mining (cs.LG).
